General Usage¶

[4]:

from Hi_LASSO_pyspark import HiLASSO_Spark

model = HiLASSO_Spark(X, y, q1 = 'auto', q2 = 'auto', B = 'auto', d = 0.05, alpha = 0.95)
model.fit(significance_level = 0.05)
